cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the implementation and evaluation of a new MAC protocol for WLANs, which aims to reduce collisions and improve network efficiency. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves the use of open firmware for wireless network cards, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The experimental evaluation of the proposed protocol also involves measuring network performance metrics such as throughput and losses, which could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the security aspect of WLANs by proposing a new contention mechanism, which could be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
